# Testing Principles

## 1. Testing shows the presence of defects, not the absence of defects
Testing can find defects, but it cannot prove that software is perfect.

## 2. Exhaustive testing is impossible
It is not realistic to test every possible input, path, and scenario.

## 3. Early testing saves time and money
The earlier a problem is found, the cheaper and easier it is to fix.

## 4. Defects cluster together
A small number of modules often contain most of the defects.

## 5. Tests wear out
Repeating the same old tests again and again reduces their ability to find new defects.

## 6. Testing is context dependent
Different products and risks require different testing approaches.

## 7. Absence of defects is a fallacy
A product may have few bugs and still fail because it is not useful or does not meet user needs.
